images.alt: A 24-year-old elegant androgynous tomboy with a boyish shape, toned midriff, and visible flat abs, standing in a neo-brutalist sky lobby of a Zurich high-rise in 2124--its walls a fusion of recycled carbon-fiber panels and self-repairing bio-concrete, bathed in the soft glow of holographic cityscapes beyond the floor-to-ceiling windows. She wears a minimalist, tech-infused ensemble that defines 2124’s street-luxe aesthetic: a cropped, climate-adaptive top (woven from lab-grown spider silk, its surface shifting between matte black and iridescent silver to regulate temperature), paired with high-waisted, modular cargo pants made from upcycled spacecraft materials, their magnetic seams adjusting to her movements. Her ankle boots are crafted from biodegradable nano-leather, their anti-grav soles hovering just above the ground. Slung over her shoulder is the IT Bag of 2124--a sleek, geometric 'Neo-Pod' by Zurich-based label Helvetia X. The bag is crafted from self-healing polymer and embedded with a mini terrarium of extraterrestrial plants on its front panel, their bioluminescent leaves pulsing in sync with her smartwatch’s biometric readouts. The bag’s modular straps double as a portable charger for her holographic sketchpad, which floats beside her, displaying 3D renders of her latest OpenSim avatar designs. The sky lobby’s floating furniture and zero-gravity art installations reflect the clean lines of her outfit, while a fractured neon sign in the background reads 'CODE THE FUTURE' in Swiss German slang. The scene is ultra-modern yet raw: high-contrast lighting sculpts her defined abs and the architectural angles of the space, with dappled reflections from the holographic billboards outside casting dynamic shadows. The color palette is sophisticated and futuristic: gunmetal grays, electric blues, and deep greens, with hyper-detailed textures emphasizing the fusion of sustainability and cutting-edge tech. A sculptural ceramic pitcher shaped like a stylized bird stands centered against a clean, light gray background. The body is rounded and bulbous at the base, tapering gently upward into a long, curved neck that extends forward into a pointed orange beak forming the spout. The surface is glossy and highly reflective, with bright highlights tracing the contours of the glaze.

The color palette is predominantly vibrant green, divided into lighter lime tones and deeper forest shades. Along the front of the pitcher, a darker green panel features subtle swirling textures embedded beneath the glaze, adding dimensional detail. A painted motif resembling layered leaves or petals in yellow-green sits prominently on the lower front, echoing natural forms.

A single large, stylized eye is positioned near the top of the body, slightly exaggerated and outlined for expressive effect. At the back, a smooth, curved handle arcs gracefully from the upper body down toward the midsection, completing the functional silhouette. Small horn-like protrusions extend from the crown of the head, giving the bird an imaginative, almost mythical character.
